<ol>
<li id="fn1"><p>Nouns in -ις (or -υς) which do not have the accent on
the final syllable of the stem (i.e.&nbsp;on the ι or υ) have an accusative
singular in -ιν (-in), e.g.&nbsp;χάριν, not χάριδα.<a href="#fnref1" class="footnote-back" role="doc-backlink">↩︎</a></p></li>
</ol>
